  "title": "ELECTRICAL ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Electrical site engineers direct and oversee electrical engineering projects at construction sites, resolving issues and ensuring that work is completed according to specifications.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead electrical engineering projects on construction sites to deliver solutions that meet design specifications and regulatory standards</li><li>Design and develop detailed electrical plans to support project objectives and compliance requirements</li><li>Monitor and coordinate contractors’ work to ensure timely and quality completion of electrical installations</li><li>Ensure all electrical plans and site work comply with local and national electrical codes to maintain safety and regulatory adherence</li><li>Conduct comprehensive testing on electrical equipment and systems to verify functionality and safety before project completion</li><li>Diagnose electrical or mechanical malfunctions in operational equipment and implement preventative and corrective maintenance to minimize downtime</li><li>Perform final inspections of electrical systems to confirm readiness for handover and operational use</li></ul>",
